# CODEX: CHAOS

## 1. DETACHMENT FACTIONS
A Chaos army is constructed using one or more **DETACHMENTS**. When adding a **DETACHMENT** to your army, you must select its **DETACHMENT FACTION**. This dictates the core units available, how it interacts with the **FORCE ORGANIZATION CHART**, and the specific special rules it utilizes. 

* **Chaos Space Marines:** The elite Traitor Legions and renegade chapters. Units in this detachment utilize the ***Veterans of the Long War*** and **Marks of Chaos** special rules. 
* **The Lost and the Damned:** Massive hordes of mortal cultists, mutants, and traitor Astra Militarum. 
* **Daemonic Incursion:** Pure manifestations of the warp. Unlike Daemons taken as reserves in other detachments, units in this detachment are not required to use the ***Daemonic Summoning*** rule and may deploy normally or use standard **RESERVES**. 
* **Dark Mechanicum:** The corrupted tech-priests of the Eye of Terror. This detachment prioritizes heavy armor, **WALKERS**, and **DAEMON ENGINES**.

---

## 2. CHAOS FACTION RULES

***Veterans of the Long War***: Models with this special rule increase their Leadership characteristic by +1 (to a maximum of 10) and possess the ***Hatred (Space Marines)*** special rule. Furthermore, any **UNIT** entirely composed of models with this rule is eligible to purchase **VETERAN SKILLS**. 

**Note on Hatred targets:** For the purposes of this rule, "Space Marines" includes any **UNIT** drawn from Codex: Space Marines, Codex: Blood Angels, Codex: Dark Angels, Codex: Space Wolves, or the Indomitus Crusade Codex.

#### **VETERAN SKILLS**
Units with access to **VETERAN SKILLS** may purchase upgrades from the following list of Universal Special Rules at the points cost indicated in their unit entry. 
* ***Counter-Attack***
* ***Furious Charge***
* ***Infiltrate***
* ***Monster Hunter***
* ***Relentless***
* ***Tank Hunters***

***Daemonic Summoning***: Units with this special rule cannot be deployed on the battlefield at the start of the game and must be placed in **RESERVE**. When a unit with this rule arrives from **RESERVE**, it must enter play using the **DEEP STRIKE** rules with the following modifications:
* The **CENTER MODEL** of the **DEEP STRIKE** must be placed within 6" of a friendly model equipped with a **Personal Icon** that was on the battlefield at the start of the current turn. 
* The unit does not roll for **SCATTER**. 
* **If there are no friendly models with a Personal Icon on the battlefield when the unit arrives from reserve, the unit is destroyed.**

***Daemonic Possession (Greater Daemons)***: Greater Daemons are kept in **RESERVE** and do not roll to arrive normally. Instead, at the start of any of your **MOVEMENT PHASES**, you may choose to automatically summon a Greater Daemon by sacrificing a friendly model with the **Champion of Chaos** special rule. 
* Remove the chosen Champion from the battlefield as a casualty. **No saves of any kind are allowed, and this does not trigger a casualty test.**
* Place the Greater Daemon model so its base is occupying the exact position the Champion was in. 

***Daemonic Possession (Vehicles)***: A **VEHICLE** with this special rule ignores the effects of **CREW SHAKEN** and **CREW STUNNED** damage results on a D6 roll of a 2+. However, the vehicle suffers a -1 modifier to its **BALLISTIC SKILL** characteristic (to a minimum of BS 1).

