## 3. MARKS OF CHAOS

A **UNIT** may only ever have one Mark of Chaos. If a **UNIT** purchases a Mark, all models in the **UNIT** must be upgraded.

#### **Infantry and Walker Effects**
* **Mark of Khorne:** Models gain +1 Attack and ***Furious Charge***.
* **Mark of Nurgle:** Models gain +1 Toughness.
* **Mark of Slaanesh:** Models gain +1 Initiative and ***Feel No Pain (6+)***.
* **Mark of Tzeentch:** Models gain a 6+ **INVULNERABLE SAVE**. If the model already has an **INVULNERABLE SAVE**, it is improved by +1 (max 3+).
* **Mark of Chaos Undivided:** Models may re-roll failed **MORALE**, **PINNING**, and **BREAK TESTS**. 

#### **Non-Walker Vehicle Effects**
* **Mark of Khorne:** Any enemy unit that successfully completes a **CHARGE** against this vehicle immediately suffers D6 Strength 4 AP- hits before melee attacks are resolved.
* **Mark of Nurgle:** The vehicle gains **+1 STRUCTURE POINT**. 
* **Mark of Slaanesh:** Enemy units within 12" of the vehicle cannot perform **STAND & SHOOT!** or **RETURN FIRE!** reactions.
* **Mark of Tzeentch:** The vehicle gains a 6+ **COVER SAVE** against shooting. If already receiving a **COVER SAVE**, improve the save by +1.
* **Mark of Chaos Undivided:** The vehicle automatically passes Leadership tests required to **SPLIT FIRE**.

